===Etymology===
[[File:Camelus dromedarius près de Mérindol 2.JPG|thumb|A dromedary (''[[Camelus dromedarius]]'')]]

{{PIE root|en|drem}}
From {{inh|en|enm|dromedari}}, {{m|enm|dromedarie|t=dromedary; any camel}}{{nb...|dromadary, dromadayr, drombodary, dromendari, dromidare, dromidarie, dromider, dromodari, dromodarie, dromodarye, dromondari, dromondarie, dromondary, dromounday, dromydary, dromyder, drowmondere|otherforms=1}},<ref>{{R:MED Online|entry=dromedārī(e|pos=n|id=MED12677}}</ref> from {{der|en|fro|dromedaire}}, from {{der|en|LL.|dromedārius|t=kind of camel}}, from {{der|en|la|*dromadārius}}, from {{m|la|dromas}}, {{m|la|dromadis|t=dromedary}} + {{m|la|-ārius|pos=suffix forming {{glossary|noun}}s denoting agents of use}}. ''Dromas'' and ''dromadis'' are derived from {{der|en|grc|δρομᾰ́ς|t=running; dromedary}}, an {{glossary|ellipsis}} of {{m|grc|[[δρομάς|δρομὰς]] [[κάμηλος]]|t=running camel}} (also compare {{m|grc|δρομάδα|t=runner; dromedary}}),<ref>{{R:OED Online|pos=n|id=57840|date=1897|nodot=yes}}; {{R:Lexico|pos=n}}</ref> from {{m|grc|δρόμος|t=race, running; race course, track}}, ultimately from {{der|en|ine-pro|*drem-|t=to run}}.

